00:22:43,782 --> 00:22:47,589
<i>I- I brought you a clean shirt.</i>

245
00:22:47,590 --> 00:22:51,077
- Molly, what's happening?
- I can't- I can't-

246
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:54,458
<i>Somebody, help!</i>

247
00:23:01,222 --> 00:23:05,316
Are you feeling better?
I was off campus at a meeting.

248
00:23:05,317 --> 00:23:07,365
I'm Dr. Emerson.

249
00:23:07,366 --> 00:23:10,789
I guess you got sidetracked on your way
to our appointment yesterday.

250
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:13,220
I understand.

251
00:23:13,221 --> 00:23:16,036
I imagine it must be overwhelming
on your first day of classes...

252
00:23:16,037 --> 00:23:17,956
but your father insisted.

253
00:23:17,957 --> 00:23:20,133
- He worries a lot.
- I hope you don't mind.

254
00:23:20,134 --> 00:23:22,437
It's still technically sealed.

255
00:23:22,438 --> 00:23:25,372
But everything stays between
you and me, all right?

256
00:23:26,309 --> 00:23:28,227
I don't need to be here.

257
00:23:28,228 --> 00:23:31,877
Heard you had a panic attack in class today.
You wanna tell me about it?

258
00:23:31,878 --> 00:23:33,829
It was just a nosebleed.

259
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:36,805
Just got freaked out
by all the blood, that's all.

260
00:23:36,806 --> 00:23:41,125
Must be hard being new at school
even under the best of circumstances.

261
00:23:41,126 --> 00:23:44,260
<i>I'm new here too.
It's hard for me.</i>

262
00:23:44,261 --> 00:23:46,597
How are you feeling otherwise?

263
00:23:46,598 --> 00:23:49,348
Whatever it says in there,
I'm not like her.

264
00:23:49,349 --> 00:23:52,677
<i>We're not suggesting that, Molly.
Our only concern is you.</i>

265
00:23:52,678 --> 00:23:56,255
Well, I told you, I'm fine.

266
00:23:56,836 --> 00:23:58,756
Your mother stabbed you
in the chest...

267
00:23:58,757 --> 00:24:00,676
with a pair of scissors.

268
00:24:00,677 --> 00:24:02,948
There was no sign of mental illness...

269
00:24:02,949 --> 00:24:04,773
<i>no warning.</i>

270
00:24:04,774 --> 00:24:06,691
I don't remember, okay?

271
00:24:06,692 --> 00:24:10,149
<i>Everyone keeps asking me what happened,
and I don't remember.</i>

272
00:24:10,150 --> 00:24:14,244
<i>- She's locked up, and she can't get out.
- Are you interested in knowing...</i>

273
00:24:14,245 --> 00:24:16,961
what her diagnosis is?

274
00:24:21,540 --> 00:24:23,940
<i>"Probable psychotic disorder.</i>

275
00:24:23,941 --> 00:24:25,987
"Signs of paranoid schizophrenia...

276
00:24:25,988 --> 00:24:29,829
or a schizo-affective disorder
accompanied by a bipolar disorder. "

277
00:24:29,830 --> 00:24:32,547
I get it.
She's crazy.

278
00:24:32,548 --> 00:24:34,883
It's okay to be scared, Molly.

279
00:24:34,884 --> 00:24:36,484
What?

280
00:24:36,485 --> 00:24:38,916
Of developing the same symptoms.

281
00:24:38,917 --> 00:24:42,437
<i>There is a genetic component
to this disease.</i>

282
00:24:42,472 --> 00:24:45,348
We're gonna keep an eye on you.

283
00:24:45,349 --> 00:24:47,901
We're not gonna let anything
happen to you.

284
00:26:02,757 --> 00:26:04,548
Books?

285
00:26:04,549 --> 00:26:08,836
<i>You're lookin' up shit in books?
Isn't that what computers are for?</i>

286
00:26:08,837 --> 00:26:13,155
Uh, compu-
Schools, um, track...

287
00:26:13,156 --> 00:26:15,172
everything you look up
on the computer.

288
00:26:15,173 --> 00:26:17,443
You know, standard procedure.

289
00:26:17,444 --> 00:26:21,339
Well, I guess I didn't peg you
as the paranoid type.

290
00:26:22,469 --> 00:26:24,164
I'm not.

291
00:26:24,165 --> 00:26:27,715
I just don't like people
keeping a record of my thoughts.

292
00:26:27,716 --> 00:26:29,732
Oh.

293
00:26:29,733 --> 00:26:33,411
<i>"Medical Diagnostic Manual
of Mental Disorders"?</i>

294
00:26:33,412 --> 00:26:35,331
What?
You don't need this.

295
00:26:35,332 --> 00:26:37,284
I can diagnose you.

296
00:26:37,285 --> 00:26:39,909
Yeah. Ooh.

297
00:26:39,910 --> 00:26:42,627
This is not good.
It's, um...

298
00:26:42,628 --> 00:26:44,548
Ebola.

299
00:26:47,204 --> 00:26:49,476
- Good call.
- Yeah, well, it was, uh...

300
00:26:49,477 --> 00:26:51,460
kind of the nosebleed
that gave you away.

301
00:26:51,461 --> 00:26:53,380
Yeah.

302
00:26:53,381 --> 00:26:56,388
- Too bad you only have six hours to live.
- Too bad.

303
00:26:56,389 --> 00:26:59,427
Well, maybe now,
you'll let me give you a ride home...

304
00:26:59,428 --> 00:27:01,604
since we don't have
that much time left.

305
00:27:05,413 --> 00:27:10,115
Since it's terminal,
I guess I can make an exception.

306
00:27:10,116 --> 00:27:13,532
Well, good.
Let's go.

307
00:27:15,333 --> 00:27:17,252
<i>So are you good friends
with that Alexis girl?</i>

308
00:27:17,253 --> 00:27:19,459
No. Why?

309
00:27:19,460 --> 00:27:22,052
I don't know.
Just wondering.

310
00:27:22,053 --> 00:27:24,194
She's nice to me, that's all.

311
00:27:24,195 --> 00:27:27,075
Nice?
I can be nice.

312
00:27:27,076 --> 00:27:28,963
Hey.

313
00:27:28,964 --> 00:27:32,388
- What the hell happened?
- Nothing.

314
00:27:32,389 --> 00:27:34,436
You had a nosebleed.
You started hyperventilating.

315
00:27:34,437 --> 00:27:36,003
You had a panic attack.
That's nothing?

316
00:27:36,004 --> 00:27:38,594
I'll just see you tomorrow, Molly.
It's fine.

317
00:27:38,595 --> 00:27:40,515
Molly, how do you think
that makes me feel-

318
00:27:40,516 --> 00:27:44,792
to know that my daughter is hurt
and bleeding and won't even call me?

319
00:28:02,755 --> 00:28:05,957
I'm sorry. I-I overreacted.

320
00:28:05,958 --> 00:28:09,572
I'm worried about you, that's all.

321
00:28:09,573 --> 00:28:11,556
You never used to worry.

322
00:28:11,557 --> 00:28:13,603
You never paid attention to me at all.

323
00:28:13,604 --> 00:28:15,876
Stop trying to control my life.

324
00:28:15,877 --> 00:28:19,006
I'm not trying
to control your life.

325
00:28:28,068 --> 00:28:30,595
You went to see her?

326
00:28:30,596 --> 00:28:33,442
She's my wife.

327
00:28:34,885 --> 00:28:37,827
You need to tell me when you're not
feeling well. I need to know.

328
00:28:37,828 --> 00:28:41,603
What?
You need to know if I'm crazy too?

329
00:28:41,604 --> 00:28:43,396
Sweetie, you are not crazy.

330
00:28:43,397 --> 00:28:46,883
My head hurts. I hear things.
Everything's mixed up.

331
00:28:46,884 --> 00:28:49,187
I just-

332
00:28:51,332 --> 00:28:53,507
It was all my fault.

333
00:28:55,428 --> 00:28:57,632
Look, tomorrow I'll make
an appointment with a doctor, okay?

334
00:28:57,667 --> 00:29:01,443
We'll get you checked out.
I know that everything is gonna be fine.

335
00:29:06,372 --> 00:29:09,851
We're gonna get through this.
Okay?

336
00:30:35,652 --> 00:30:39,099
<i>Molly?</i>

337
00:30:42,628 --> 00:30:45,018
Oh, shit.

338
00:31:02,116 --> 00:31:04,538
<i>Molly?</i>

339
00:31:08,930 --> 00:31:10,847
<i>Molly?</i>

340
00:31:14,563 --> 00:31:17,025
<i>I know what you are, Molly.</i>

341
00:31:20,545 --> 00:31:24,129
Wait! Daddy!

342
00:31:24,130 --> 00:31:25,825
Daddy, help!
Let me out!

343
00:31:25,826 --> 00:31:27,712
Molly, what's going on?

344
00:31:27,713 --> 00:31:30,592
Daddy, let me out! Dad!

345
00:31:30,593 --> 00:31:33,473
Molly! Molly!

346
00:31:33,474 --> 00:31:37,986
Daddy! Daddy!

347
00:31:52,290 --> 00:31:55,998
<i>Molly? Molly, do you know where you are?</i>

348
00:31:57,602 --> 00:31:59,552
Molly, are you with me?

349
00:31:59,553 --> 00:32:02,529
Easy. Easy.
Just relax.

350
00:32:06,947 --> 00:32:09,025
How did-
What's going on?

351
00:32:09,026 --> 00:32:11,168
You're in the hospital.
Everything's all right, baby.

352
00:32:11,169 --> 00:32:13,952
- You're gonna be fine.
- How long have you been having nosebleeds?

353
00:32:13,953 --> 00:32:17,409
A while, since before Mom-

354
00:32:17,410 --> 00:32:22,145
Have you been experiencing vision problems?
Headaches? Dizziness?

355
00:32:24,706 --> 00:32:28,545
See this little spot?
It's most likely a tumor...

356
00:32:28,546 --> 00:32:30,144
<i>in your sinus cavity.</i>

357
00:32:30,145 --> 00:32:32,576
<i>A nasal hemangioma.
A little mass of blood vessels...</i>

358
00:32:32,577 --> 00:32:35,392
<i>growing out of control and creating
a whole lot of pressure in your head.</i>

359
00:32:35,393 --> 00:32:39,553
That would explain the nosebleeds,
the headaches and the vision problems.

360
00:32:39,554 --> 00:32:43,681
What about... hearing things?

361
00:32:43,682 --> 00:32:45,153
<i>Can that happen too?</i>

362
00:32:45,154 --> 00:32:48,352
Sometimes the buildup of pressure
can cause episodes of vertigo...

363
00:32:48,353 --> 00:32:51,455
or auditory hallucinations, disorientation.

364
00:32:51,457 --> 00:32:55,393
I thought I was going crazy.

365
00:32:55,394 --> 00:32:58,432
We caught it early,
so there's nothing to worry about.

366
00:32:58,433 --> 00:33:01,439
These things are pesky,
but usually benign.

367
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:03,712
<i>We'll do an endoscopic procedure...</i>

368
00:33:03,713 --> 00:33:05,791
<i>and monitor you for a few days.</i>

369
00:33:05,792 --> 00:33:08,288
<i>You don't mind missing
a little school, do you?</i>

370
00:33:08,289 --> 00:33:11,103
Good. I'll schedule the surgery
for tomorrow morning.

371
00:33:11,104 --> 00:33:13,494
Get some rest.

372
00:33:14,850 --> 00:33:17,601
You see?
Everything's gonna be all right now.

373
00:33:17,602 --> 00:33:20,797
Everything's gonna be absolutely fine.

374
00:33:57,730 --> 00:34:00,063
Is my dad here?

375
00:34:03,170 --> 00:34:05,472
Is there any water?

376
00:34:05,473 --> 00:34:07,710
I know what you are.

377
00:34:07,745 --> 00:34:10,593
It's okay. It's okay. You're okay.

378
00:34:10,594 --> 00:34:13,057
You're out of surgery now, sweetie.
Everything went really well.

379
00:34:13,058 --> 00:34:16,513
There was no complications.
The tumor's benign.

380
00:34:16,514 --> 00:34:18,432
She was here.

381
00:34:18,433 --> 00:34:20,033
- Who?
- Mom.

382
00:34:20,034 --> 00:34:21,632
No, it's just you and me.

383
00:34:21,633 --> 00:34:23,389
I saw her.
She tried-

384
00:34:23,424 --> 00:34:25,847
No, it's just the anaesthesia.

385
00:34:27,873 --> 00:34:30,719
Just go and relax.
Lie back down.

386
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:33,436
I don't suppose you feel like
having a visitor?

387
00:34:34,689 --> 00:34:38,332
- A visitor?
- Yeah, a friend from school came to see you.

388
00:34:43,201 --> 00:34:45,922
<i>Oh.</i>

389
00:34:45,923 --> 00:34:48,640
You want me to tell her to come back
when you're feeling better?

390
00:34:48,641 --> 00:34:50,561
No. It's okay.

391
00:34:50,562 --> 00:34:53,856
Okay. Come in.

392
00:34:57,280 --> 00:35:00,769
I'm gonna go scrounge up a decent meal.
You girls want anything?

393
00:35:00,770 --> 00:35:03,967
A pizza, or chili cheese fries?

394
00:35:03,968 --> 00:35:05,854
No, thanks, Mr. Hartley.

395
00:35:05,889 --> 00:35:10,206
Okay. Okay.
I'll be right back.

396
00:35:10,241 --> 00:35:13,208
- Your dad seems really nice.
- Yeah.

397
00:35:15,937 --> 00:35:17,857
My grandmother works in a hospital.

398
00:35:17,858 --> 00:35:19,873
She says flowers
make all the difference.

399
00:35:19,874 --> 00:35:22,208
How did you know I was here?

400
00:35:22,209 --> 00:35:27,161
Everyone at Huntington knows everything.
No secrets.

401
00:35:28,065 --> 00:35:31,578
- You're big news. But don't worry about it.
- What do you mean?

402
00:35:32,832 --> 00:35:35,199
I brought some homework assignments.

403
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:37,600
Thought I could help you catch up.

404
00:35:37,601 --> 00:35:40,087
Why are you so nice to me?

405
00:35:41,954 --> 00:35:45,568
Molly, can I ask you a question?

406
00:35:45,569 --> 00:35:48,318
<i>Sure.</i>

407
00:35:48,353 --> 00:35:50,687
Have you been saved?

408
00:35:52,032 --> 00:35:55,135
The doctor caught the tumor early.
I'm fine.

409
00:35:55,136 --> 00:35:57,408
That's not what I mean.

410
00:35:57,409 --> 00:35:59,584
Oh. Right.

411
00:35:59,585 --> 00:36:02,650
Have you been baptized?

412
00:36:04,321 --> 00:36:06,850
My parents don't believe
in that sort of thing.

413
00:36:06,851 --> 00:36:08,797
Well, what about you?

414
00:36:08,832 --> 00:36:11,584
This is your life, your journey.

415
00:36:11,585 --> 00:36:13,919
What do you believe?

416
00:36:16,993 --> 00:36:19,487
I'm just worried about you, that's all.

417
00:36:19,488 --> 00:36:21,663
I'm feeling a little tired.

418
00:36:21,664 --> 00:36:24,671
I brought this for you.

419
00:36:31,905 --> 00:36:34,140
Thanks.

420
00:36:35,745 --> 00:36:38,133
Sure.

421
00:36:43,841 --> 00:36:46,841
I pray for you every night.

422
00:36:56,705 --> 00:36:58,624
<i>How do you feel?</i>

423
00:36:58,625 --> 00:36:59,871
Good.

424
00:36:59,872 --> 00:37:02,335
Your birthday's coming up.
What about a party?

425
00:37:02,336 --> 00:37:04,726
A party?

426
00:37:05,441 --> 00:37:07,583
Cake, presents, a clown.

427
00:37:07,584 --> 00:37:09,855
No clown.

428
00:37:09,856 --> 00:37:13,504
You know, time rushes by
like you wouldn't believe, Molly.

429
00:37:13,505 --> 00:37:15,905
I mean, just yesterday
you were a little thing in pigtails.

430
00:37:15,940 --> 00:37:20,000
And suddenly, you're 18.
All grown up.

431
00:37:20,001 --> 00:37:22,240
You won't need me anymore.

432
00:37:22,241 --> 00:37:25,754
Don't worry.
I'll need you.

433
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:40,501
<i>¶¶</i>

434
00:37:46,912 --> 00:37:51,039
¶ Oh, the blood of Jesus ¶

435
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:55,167
¶Washes away ¶

436
00:37:55,168 --> 00:37:57,600
¶¶

437
00:37:57,601 --> 00:38:02,203
<i>Alexis, enough with
the musical interlude, please.</i>

438
00:38:04,033 --> 00:38:07,229
<i>- Sorry.
- Thank you.</i>

439
00:38:08,896 --> 00:38:12,351
I'm so glad you're back.
There's a calculus quiz tomorrow.

440
00:38:12,352 --> 00:38:14,814
<i>My grandma said I can
come over tonight and help you study.</i>

441
00:38:14,815 --> 00:38:16,416
Okay.

442
00:38:16,417 --> 00:38:19,839
- Um, I'll see you in a few minutes.
- All right.

443
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,727
Hey.

444
00:38:21,728 --> 00:38:24,767
- Welcome back.
- Thanks. Nice catch.

445
00:38:24,768 --> 00:38:27,008
I didn't think
you'd be back so soon.

446
00:38:27,009 --> 00:38:28,982
I would've definitely milked that
" brain surgery" thing for,

447
00:38:28,983 --> 00:38:30,400
like, a month off, maybe 2.

448
00:38:30,401 --> 00:38:34,687
It wasn't actually brain surgery.

449
00:38:34,688 --> 00:38:37,759
- You're better now, right? Aren't you?
- I'm fine.

450
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:40,319
Great. Then you can come
to my party tonight.

451
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:42,784
Tonight?
It's a Tuesday.

452
00:38:42,785 --> 00:38:45,567
Exactly. It's a Tuesday,
and my parents are out of town.

453
00:38:45,568 --> 00:38:48,479
I don't know.
Maybe.

454
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:50,783
Well, you'll need the secret code.

455
00:38:50,784 --> 00:38:53,727
A secret code?

456
00:38:53,728 --> 00:38:55,807
Just for the gate.

457
00:38:55,808 --> 00:38:58,196
Can't be too careful.

458
00:38:59,328 --> 00:39:01,920
Oh, and bring anyone you want
as long as it's not a guy.

459
00:39:01,921 --> 00:39:04,309
<i>Yo, yo, let's go!</i>

460
00:39:06,113 --> 00:39:09,461
Wait! Where do you live?

461
00:39:14,944 --> 00:39:18,047
Molly.
Are you feeling better?

462
00:39:18,048 --> 00:39:21,088
- Yeah. Thanks.
- Aw.

463
00:39:21,089 --> 00:39:23,775
I hope it wasn't too serious.

464
00:39:23,776 --> 00:39:25,728
No.

465
00:39:25,729 --> 00:39:28,215
So what were you and Joseph
talking about?

466
00:39:29,217 --> 00:39:32,800
- Nothing. We're just friends.
- Of course.

467
00:39:32,801 --> 00:39:38,136
It must be really difficult
to... be in your situation.

468
00:39:39,231 --> 00:39:41,686
What's that supposed to mean?

469
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:47,583
He doesn't really want you to come.

470
00:39:47,584 --> 00:39:51,518
Oh, God. I'm so sorry.
I didn't even see you there.

471
00:39:51,519 --> 00:39:53,728
You're a bitch.

472
00:39:53,729 --> 00:39:56,313
I know.

473
00:39:57,184 --> 00:39:59,966
God, I hate her.

474
00:40:00,735 --> 00:40:04,119
Do you wanna eat?

475
00:40:05,087 --> 00:40:07,008
<i>So, are you gonna go?</i>

476
00:40:07,009 --> 00:40:10,237
- To the party?
- Yeah, to the party.

477
00:40:11,969 --> 00:40:13,888
I don't know if I wanna go.

478
00:40:13,889 --> 00:40:16,479
Yeah, you do. You wanna go,
and you wanna take me with you.

479
00:40:16,480 --> 00:40:18,399
You wanna go to the party?

480
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:20,543
Please.
It's not like I even care.

481
00:40:20,544 --> 00:40:23,840
It's just-
You know, it's something to do.

482
00:40:23,841 --> 00:40:27,903
Come on. You can't tell me
you're not bored out of your mind here.

483
00:40:27,904 --> 00:40:30,719
You can count, right?

484
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:33,632
- So then what's your curfew for tonight?
- Curfew?

485
00:40:33,633 --> 00:40:35,263
Molly!

486
00:40:35,264 --> 00:40:39,006
- Over here.
- I don't, um-

487
00:40:39,007 --> 00:40:44,954
I don't really do the cafeteria thing.
So... call me later.

488
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:49,406
Ditch the Bible thumper.

489
00:40:51,937 --> 00:40:57,402
<i>¶¶</i>

490
00:40:58,047 --> 00:40:59,967
<i>Molly?</i>

491
00:40:59,968 --> 00:41:04,092
<i>Hello?</i>

492
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:07,742
Where did you say you were going?

