00:41:07,743 --> 00:41:10,231
Um, study group.

494
00:41:11,039 --> 00:41:12,958
<i>It might go a little late.</i>

495
00:41:12,959 --> 00:41:16,480
Um, we have a big test tomorrow.
Calculus.

496
00:41:16,481 --> 00:41:18,399
Are you sure you're up for this?

497
00:41:18,400 --> 00:41:21,824
You're the one who said
I was perfectly fine, remember?

498
00:41:21,825 --> 00:41:24,889
Plus, I need to catch up.

499
00:41:27,104 --> 00:41:30,432
- Not too late.
- Not too late. Got it.

500
00:41:30,433 --> 00:41:33,439
<i>¶ Oh, let the sky be gray ¶</i>

501
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:36,606
<i>¶ 'Cause if it's ever
gonna get any better¶</i>

502
00:41:36,607 --> 00:41:39,738
<i>¶ It's gotta get worse for a day ¶¶</i>

503
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:46,942
Let's go.

504
00:41:46,943 --> 00:41:49,150
Hey.

505
00:41:49,151 --> 00:41:52,703
You forgettin' somethin'?

506
00:41:52,704 --> 00:41:55,488
Dad, this is Leah.
This is my dad.

507
00:41:55,489 --> 00:41:58,078
<i>- Hey, Dad.
- It's nice to meet you, Leah.</i>

508
00:41:58,079 --> 00:42:02,463
- Make sure she doesn't study too hard.
- Yeah, that won't be a problem.

509
00:42:02,464 --> 00:42:05,976
Okay.
Keep your phone on.

510
00:42:10,367 --> 00:42:12,756
Nice outfit.

511
00:42:16,223 --> 00:42:18,296
Better.

512
00:42:20,895 --> 00:42:23,070
Do you know where he lives?

513
00:42:23,071 --> 00:42:25,951
Come on. Everybody knows
where Joseph Young lives.

514
00:42:25,952 --> 00:42:29,023
His father owns, like, half the city.
You didn't know that?

515
00:42:29,024 --> 00:42:30,943
No.

516
00:42:30,944 --> 00:42:33,823
Well, Suzie's not gonna let you
have him without a fight, so-

517
00:42:33,824 --> 00:42:35,996
Who says I want him?

518
00:42:36,031 --> 00:42:38,999
Yeah. Okay.
That was convincing. Good job.

519
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:43,988
I saw you in Emerson's office
the other day.

520
00:42:44,575 --> 00:42:46,494
Oh, really?

521
00:42:46,495 --> 00:42:48,990
So what, does that mean
we're sharing now?

522
00:42:48,991 --> 00:42:53,748
Should we read each other's journals
and promise to be best friends forever?

523
00:42:56,031 --> 00:42:59,740
I have- I have anger issues.

524
00:43:00,639 --> 00:43:05,822
My father died
of throat cancer last year.

525
00:43:05,823 --> 00:43:09,823
<i>Then when he's dead I find out
he's not even really my father.</i>

526
00:43:09,824 --> 00:43:12,704
Turns out I'm adopted.

527
00:43:12,705 --> 00:43:15,742
My real parents, they gave me up.

528
00:43:15,743 --> 00:43:18,750
<i>They just didn't
feel like keeping me.</i>

529
00:43:18,751 --> 00:43:22,271
So what about you?
You got low self-esteem?

530
00:43:22,272 --> 00:43:25,342
Or, uh, mild depression?

531
00:43:25,343 --> 00:43:30,612
<i>Or maybe a weird
psychosexual disorder?</i>

532
00:43:35,712 --> 00:43:38,460
My mom tried to kill me.

533
00:43:39,839 --> 00:43:44,030
She stabbed me in the bathroom
one day after school.

534
00:43:44,031 --> 00:43:46,811
Right.

535
00:43:51,999 --> 00:43:54,486
You're screwing with me.

536
00:43:55,776 --> 00:43:59,900
She's locked in that psych ward
outside of town.

537
00:44:00,768 --> 00:44:03,100
Clayton.

538
00:44:03,135 --> 00:44:06,647
Dad wanted to move here
to make a fresh new start.

539
00:44:08,543 --> 00:44:11,410
So here we are.

540
00:44:15,742 --> 00:44:17,886
You win.

541
00:44:17,887 --> 00:44:20,603
<i>¶¶</i>

542
00:44:21,247 --> 00:44:23,758
- Stop. What is it?
- 6-5-2-2.

543
00:44:23,793 --> 00:44:26,269
<i>¶¶</i>

544
00:44:26,270 --> 00:44:28,222
Oh, my gosh.
This is great.

545
00:44:30,208 --> 00:44:33,022
<i>You do have anger issues.</i>

546
00:44:33,023 --> 00:44:37,245
<i>¶¶</i>

547
00:44:39,583 --> 00:44:43,412
<i>¶¶</i>

548
00:44:57,471 --> 00:44:59,390
Hey!

549
00:44:59,391 --> 00:45:01,310
I wasn't sure you'd show up.

550
00:45:01,311 --> 00:45:03,646
- Leah talked me into it.
- You are so welcome.

551
00:45:03,647 --> 00:45:06,558
Do you seriously know,
like, all of these people?

552
00:45:06,559 --> 00:45:09,982
- No. Should I?
- Probably.

553
00:45:09,983 --> 00:45:13,331
- Do you want a drink?
- Um... sure.

554
00:45:13,951 --> 00:45:15,902
Okay, I can take a hint.
See ya.

555
00:45:15,903 --> 00:45:18,455
- Wait!
- Hey, follow me.

556
00:45:20,798 --> 00:45:23,677
<i>¶¶</i>

557
00:45:23,678 --> 00:45:25,597
So, what do you want to drink?

558
00:45:25,598 --> 00:45:27,519
I don't know.

559
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:29,919
I'm gonna surprise you.

560
00:45:29,920 --> 00:45:33,714
<i>You're rich.
Rich rich.</i>

561
00:45:34,527 --> 00:45:37,395
<i>Well, I hope you don't
hold it against me.</i>

562
00:45:39,647 --> 00:45:41,566
So, where's Suzie?

563
00:45:41,567 --> 00:45:43,838
I don't know.
Why?

564
00:45:43,839 --> 00:45:45,983
Just wondering.

565
00:45:45,984 --> 00:45:50,718
- You know we broke up, right?
- No, I- I didn't know that.

566
00:45:50,719 --> 00:45:52,637
Yeah.
Things change.

567
00:45:52,638 --> 00:45:55,092
People change.

568
00:45:55,648 --> 00:45:57,662
You look different out of uniform.

569
00:45:57,663 --> 00:45:59,805
That's a compliment, right?

570
00:45:59,806 --> 00:46:03,390
Of course.
Here, try this.

571
00:46:03,391 --> 00:46:05,693
To things changing.

572
00:46:09,535 --> 00:46:12,917
Mmm.
You feel like dancing?

573
00:46:15,744 --> 00:46:19,572
<i>¶¶</i>

574
00:46:30,750 --> 00:46:32,829
This party's crazy.

575
00:46:32,830 --> 00:46:34,750
In a good way.

576
00:46:34,751 --> 00:46:36,669
It's all right, I guess, huh?

577
00:46:36,670 --> 00:46:38,589
Don't your parents mind?

578
00:46:38,590 --> 00:46:41,981
Let's not talk about my parents.

579
00:46:41,982 --> 00:46:45,115
- But I'm really glad you decided to show up.
- Me, too.

580
00:46:45,116 --> 00:46:47,037
<i>- Dude!
- What?</i>

581
00:46:47,038 --> 00:46:50,236
That hairy guy from Lincoln just stuffed
a package of frozen burritos down the toilet.

582
00:46:50,237 --> 00:46:52,956
- What?
- You got a plunger or something?

583
00:46:52,957 --> 00:46:55,036
<i>Yeah, um, I do.</i>

584
00:46:55,037 --> 00:46:57,790
Hold on. Will you stay right here
while I go and fix this, please?

585
00:46:57,825 --> 00:47:00,725
I'm sorry. I'll be right back,
I promise. Okay?

586
00:47:03,391 --> 00:47:06,259
<i>¶¶</i>

587
00:47:09,117 --> 00:47:11,485
What the hell are you doing here?

588
00:47:11,486 --> 00:47:13,277
Your ex-boyfriend invited me.

589
00:47:13,278 --> 00:47:16,188
My ex-boyfriend?

590
00:47:16,189 --> 00:47:20,797
<i>Am I supposed to be shocked?
Am I supposed to run away crying?</i>

591
00:47:20,798 --> 00:47:22,717
<i>Am I supposed to be scared?</i>

592
00:47:22,718 --> 00:47:25,848
Everyone knows you're
a mental case, Molly.

593
00:47:26,430 --> 00:47:27,998
Just like your mother.

594
00:47:30,141 --> 00:47:32,637
<i>Fight back, girl!</i>

595
00:47:32,638 --> 00:47:34,612
Go to hell.

596
00:47:36,509 --> 00:47:38,780
Stay away from my boyfriend!

597
00:47:38,781 --> 00:47:42,046
I don't like to be threatened!

598
00:47:44,446 --> 00:47:47,030
You bitch!

599
00:47:47,709 --> 00:47:50,780
Leave... me... alone!

600
00:47:54,718 --> 00:47:56,954
<i>Messed her up!</i>

601
00:48:01,087 --> 00:48:03,004
<i>There's no way.</i>

602
00:48:03,005 --> 00:48:06,046
<i>So he gets sent for, like,
three weeks and he cries-</i>

603
00:48:06,047 --> 00:48:08,509
- I wanna go home.
- What?

604
00:48:08,510 --> 00:48:10,237
I want to go home.

605
00:48:10,238 --> 00:48:13,660
Okay. Okay. Well,
I'm not ready to go yet.

606
00:48:13,661 --> 00:48:17,500
If it weren't for me, you wouldn't
even be here. I got you invited.

607
00:48:17,501 --> 00:48:20,637
Sorry. I think I'm too wasted
to drive you home.

608
00:48:20,638 --> 00:48:23,124
Ask your new boyfriend.

609
00:48:27,069 --> 00:48:29,628
Molly! Molly, wait.

610
00:48:29,629 --> 00:48:32,084
I didn't mean it.
I-

611
00:48:40,637 --> 00:48:42,429
<i>Shit!</i>

612
00:48:46,685 --> 00:48:48,860
- Hey.
- Dad?

613
00:48:48,861 --> 00:48:52,220
Where the hell are you? I've been trying
to call you. You have to leave your phone on.

614
00:48:52,221 --> 00:48:54,620
I'm sorry.
I need you to come pick me up.

615
00:48:54,621 --> 00:48:57,404
- Not sure- am-
- Molly?

616
00:48:57,405 --> 00:49:00,379
Dad? Dad?

617
00:49:00,380 --> 00:49:02,589
Are you there?

618
00:49:02,590 --> 00:49:05,207
Molly!

619
00:50:01,917 --> 00:50:03,836
Molly?

620
00:50:03,837 --> 00:50:08,313
I'm at a pay phone.
It's 145 F-Fairpoint Drive.

621
00:50:08,348 --> 00:50:12,764
It's, um, right across from
an old barbecue restaurant.

622
00:50:12,765 --> 00:50:15,068
Are you safe?

623
00:50:15,069 --> 00:50:18,364
Yeah.
Yeah, I'm safe.

624
00:50:18,365 --> 00:50:21,085
Okay. Go inside the restaurant
and wait for me right there.

625
00:50:21,086 --> 00:50:23,229
I'm leaving right now.
You understand?

626
00:50:23,230 --> 00:50:26,076
<i>Okay.</i>

627
00:50:32,989 --> 00:50:36,764
I know what you are, and I can't let you be
filled with the darkness! Do you understand?

628
00:50:36,765 --> 00:50:40,726
Molly! Molly!

629
00:50:42,526 --> 00:50:46,037
Molly!
Let me save you!

630
00:50:48,348 --> 00:50:50,967
Mom?

631
00:50:55,517 --> 00:50:59,261
Where are you?
Where are you?

632
00:50:59,262 --> 00:51:01,403
Where are you?

633
00:51:01,404 --> 00:51:04,061
- Where is she?
- Hey, are you all right?

634
00:51:04,062 --> 00:51:07,672
Where is she?
Where is she? Where is she?

635
00:51:10,844 --> 00:51:13,724
<i>Go ahead
and make that an attempted code one.</i>

636
00:51:23,358 --> 00:51:25,276
Molly.

637
00:51:25,277 --> 00:51:27,388
- She was here.
- No.

638
00:51:27,389 --> 00:51:29,307
Yes.

639
00:51:29,308 --> 00:51:30,909
I know what I saw!

640
00:51:30,910 --> 00:51:33,085
Sweetheart, I called Clayton.
She's in her room.

641
00:51:33,086 --> 00:51:35,637
She's been in her room all night.

642
00:51:41,661 --> 00:51:43,643
I'm scared.

643
00:51:43,644 --> 00:51:46,236
Don't be scared.
I'm right here.

644
00:51:46,237 --> 00:51:48,920
That's not good enough.

645
00:51:49,404 --> 00:51:51,794
Everything is gonna be all right.

646
00:52:11,517 --> 00:52:13,905
<i>Suzie.</i>

647
00:52:16,925 --> 00:52:19,160
I'm really sorry.

648
00:52:20,253 --> 00:52:22,235
I know what you are.

649
00:52:22,236 --> 00:52:25,018
What?

650
00:52:27,516 --> 00:52:29,906
<i>What am I?</i>

651
00:52:30,717 --> 00:52:33,716
What am I?

652
00:52:41,021 --> 00:52:42,941
Molly, hey, are you okay?

653
00:52:42,942 --> 00:52:46,716
I've been so worried about you. I left
you messages. Why didn't you call me back?

654
00:52:46,717 --> 00:52:48,636
I don't know.

655
00:52:48,637 --> 00:52:51,516
What happened that night
at the party?

656
00:52:51,517 --> 00:52:53,627
I didn't mean to hurt her.

657
00:52:53,628 --> 00:52:57,654
Molly, I don't care about what happened to
Suzie. I care about what happened to you.

658
00:52:58,556 --> 00:53:00,476
I don't know what happened!

659
00:53:00,477 --> 00:53:04,372
- I-
- You can tell me. Just talk to me. It's okay.

660
00:53:07,038 --> 00:53:09,590
Please.

661
00:53:10,364 --> 00:53:12,284
Just leave me alone.

662
00:53:12,285 --> 00:53:15,633
- Everyone should just leave me alone.
- Molly!

663
00:53:16,669 --> 00:53:18,588
<i>It felt real.</i>

664
00:53:18,589 --> 00:53:20,539
But you understand that it wasn't.

665
00:53:20,540 --> 00:53:23,227
What is happening to me?

666
00:53:23,228 --> 00:53:27,068
Fear is a very powerful emotion, Molly.
Plays tricks with your mind.

667
00:53:27,069 --> 00:53:31,099
It makes you see things and hear things
that aren't really there.

668
00:53:31,100 --> 00:53:34,747
Nothing is wrong with you.
You're perfectly normal.

669
00:53:34,748 --> 00:53:36,886
Nothing about me is normal!

670
00:53:37,789 --> 00:53:41,659
- Why did she try to kill me?
- Your mother is very ill.

671
00:53:41,660 --> 00:53:45,660
She's not in her right mind. She's not
thinking clearly. Do you understand that?

672
00:53:45,661 --> 00:53:49,172
We're gonna
work through this together.

673
00:53:51,229 --> 00:53:53,148
Okay.

674
00:53:53,149 --> 00:53:56,347
Here.
I want you to take this.

675
00:53:56,348 --> 00:53:59,484
I want you to call that number
any time you need to talk.

676
00:53:59,485 --> 00:54:02,075
I'm here for you.

677
00:54:02,076 --> 00:54:04,465
Okay.

678
00:54:08,540 --> 00:54:10,619
Molly.

679
00:54:10,620 --> 00:54:12,540
Look, I'm really sorry, okay?

680
00:54:12,541 --> 00:54:16,123
I should've taken you home
the other night.

681
00:54:16,124 --> 00:54:18,512
It doesn't matter.

682
00:54:19,965 --> 00:54:22,525
But it's your birthday tomorrow.

683
00:54:22,526 --> 00:54:25,372
I mean, let's-
let's do something.

684
00:54:32,860 --> 00:54:34,843
Molly!

685
00:54:34,844 --> 00:54:36,444
<i>Hi.</i>

686
00:54:36,445 --> 00:54:40,060
I need to get home.
I'm sorry.

687
00:54:40,061 --> 00:54:41,979
I know about the party.

688
00:54:41,980 --> 00:54:44,796
I know what happened.
Suzie Woods told me everything.

689
00:54:44,797 --> 00:54:46,907
<i>Doesn't matter.</i>

690
00:54:46,908 --> 00:54:50,617
I'm not mad you ditched me.
Honest.

691
00:54:51,933 --> 00:54:55,129
You should come inside.

692
00:54:56,572 --> 00:54:58,267
I can't.

693
00:54:58,268 --> 00:55:00,188
Whatever you're going through,
we can help.

694
00:55:00,189 --> 00:55:04,571
If you're lost,
if you're afraid, we can help.

695
00:55:04,572 --> 00:55:08,987
If you accept Christ into your heart,
you'll be blessed with eternal salvation...

696
00:55:08,988 --> 00:55:11,163
<i>spiritual protection, grace.</i>

697
00:55:11,164 --> 00:55:13,554
Isn't that what you want?

698
00:55:14,365 --> 00:55:18,139
You're a good person, Molly.
Let me help.

699
00:55:42,140 --> 00:55:44,060
Hi, you've reached
Robert Hartley's cell phone.

700
00:55:44,061 --> 00:55:47,195
I'm unavailable to take your call right now,
but if you leave me a message...

701
00:55:47,196 --> 00:55:49,594
I'll call you as soon as I can.

702
00:55:49,595 --> 00:55:52,955
I'm home. You told me to call
when I got here, so I'm calling.

703
00:57:08,668 --> 00:57:11,004
Stupid lock.

704
00:57:11,005 --> 00:57:14,075
Get away from me!

705
00:57:14,076 --> 00:57:16,442
Molly, the nurse let me out.

706
00:57:16,443 --> 00:57:19,066
She let me out because she believes.

707
00:57:19,067 --> 00:57:20,828
What do you want from me?

708
00:57:20,829 --> 00:57:23,323
To save you.
That's all I want.

709
00:57:23,324 --> 00:57:26,202
You have no idea
what you're about to become.

710
00:57:26,203 --> 00:57:28,731
<i>Can't you feel it, Molly?</i>

711
00:57:28,732 --> 00:57:30,714
<i>There is evil everywhere.</i>

712
00:57:30,715 --> 00:57:33,883
The darkness is coming for you, honey.
It's coming.

713
00:57:33,884 --> 00:57:35,962
What's happening to me?

714
00:57:35,963 --> 00:57:38,522
I'm so sorry.
We made a terrible mistake.

715
00:57:38,523 --> 00:57:40,187
What?

716
00:57:40,188 --> 00:57:44,955
You were never meant to live.
We were so weak. We were so selfish.

717
00:57:44,956 --> 00:57:47,835
You died the night you were born...

718
00:57:47,836 --> 00:57:51,067
on the bathroom floor
of a restaurant.

719
00:57:51,068 --> 00:57:55,289
<i>You came too early. I never made it
to the hospital. There was too much blood.</i>

720
00:57:56,507 --> 00:58:01,339
I'd lost babies before- miscarriages-
and I couldn't lose another one.

721
00:58:01,340 --> 00:58:03,609
<i>But then this woman
suddenly appeared.</i>

722
00:58:05,244 --> 00:58:08,795
I don't know where she came from,
but suddenly she was just standing there...

723
00:58:08,796 --> 00:58:11,035
and she offered us a deal.

724
00:58:11,036 --> 00:58:13,915
She promised to make you live.

725
00:58:13,916 --> 00:58:17,819
<i>Honey, they knew you were special.
That's why she came for you.</i>

726
00:58:17,820 --> 00:58:21,595
<i>She promised us 18 years together.</i>

727
00:58:21,596 --> 00:58:23,484
And then you would belong to them.

728
00:58:23,485 --> 00:58:26,363
- I don't believe you.
- There are others like you.

729
00:58:26,364 --> 00:58:29,339
- Dad would've said something!
- No, he refuses to believe the truth!

730
00:58:29,340 --> 00:58:33,115
He made the choice, but he doesn't
understand! But I know what we did!

731
00:58:33,116 --> 00:58:35,547
I know this has happened before.

732
00:58:35,548 --> 00:58:37,467
- You're crazy!
- No, I'm not crazy!

733
00:58:37,468 --> 00:58:38,460
Yeah!

734
00:58:38,461 --> 00:58:40,347
If I don't stop you now,
you'll do terrible things.

735
00:58:40,348 --> 00:58:44,699
I just wanna make things right
before it's too late, before you turn 18.

736
00:58:44,700 --> 00:58:48,378
Don't you understand what's happening to you?
Can't you feel it?

737
00:58:48,379 --> 00:58:50,298
You're being torn from this world.

738
00:58:50,299 --> 00:58:52,858
Everything you do will be
in the service of them!

739
00:58:52,859 --> 00:58:55,867
- Your life will no longer be yours anymore!
- Shut up!

740
00:58:55,868 --> 00:58:58,362
- Don't you understand? I can save you!
- No!

741
00:58:58,363 --> 00:59:01,691
May God take you
so you can be saved!

742
00:59:02,428 --> 00:59:05,146
- Molly!
- Help! Somebody help me!

743
00:59:05,147 --> 00:59:07,962
<i>Molly!</i>

744
00:59:07,963 --> 00:59:10,683
No! I can't let you live!

745
00:59:10,684 --> 00:59:13,115
I can't let the darkness take you!

746
00:59:13,150 --> 00:59:15,547
They're coming for you!

747
00:59:15,548 --> 00:59:19,034
No! I love you!
Honey! No!

748
00:59:19,035 --> 00:59:21,969
No!

749
01:00:42,620 --> 01:00:45,717
She came back.

750
01:00:47,099 --> 01:00:49,269
She told me everything!

751
01:00:50,267 --> 01:00:52,763
What happened
the night I was born!

752
01:00:52,764 --> 01:00:54,778
What'll happen to me
on my 18th birthday!

753
01:00:54,779 --> 01:00:57,659
Molly, for God's sake, we didn't do anything!
She's delusional!

754
01:00:57,660 --> 01:01:00,985
She knew something was going to happen
to me and she tried to help me!

755
01:01:00,986 --> 01:01:02,906
She wanted to stop it!

756
01:01:02,907 --> 01:01:05,498
No!
Nothing is gonna happen to you!

757
01:01:05,499 --> 01:01:09,595
That wasn't real! That was some religious
nutcase screwing with your mother's head!

758
01:01:09,596 --> 01:01:13,305
You have to do something!
Tomorrow's my fucking birthday!

759
01:01:13,306 --> 01:01:16,379
- You can't let them take me!
- No one is gonna take you!

760
01:01:16,380 --> 01:01:18,683
<i>Now, this is exactly
how it started with your mother...</i>

761
01:01:18,684 --> 01:01:22,874
<i>with the religious delusions and the
paranoia and the losing touch with reality.</i>

762
01:01:22,875 --> 01:01:25,178
<i>She's dead because of me!</i>

763
01:01:25,179 --> 01:01:27,705
I won't let that happen again.
I won't lose you, too.

764
01:01:27,706 --> 01:01:30,193
Let go!

765
01:01:31,132 --> 01:01:33,755
I'm gonna get you some help.
A good doctor.

766
01:01:33,756 --> 01:01:37,113
<i>- Someone who can help you see the truth.
- I know the truth!</i>

767
01:01:37,114 --> 01:01:39,675
- I have to find a way to stop it!
- Then just let me help you.

768
01:01:39,676 --> 01:01:43,766
- Let me take you someplace quiet and safe.
- I won't let you lock me up!

769
01:01:51,706 --> 01:01:56,377
<i>¶Through the blood of Jesus ¶</i>

770
01:01:56,378 --> 01:02:00,794
<i>¶ Through the blood of Jesus ¶</i>

771
01:02:00,795 --> 01:02:05,242
<i>¶ Through the blood of Jesus ¶¶</i>

772
01:02:05,243 --> 01:02:08,666
<i>- ¶¶
- What are you doing here?</i>

773
01:02:08,667 --> 01:02:12,278
I need your help.
I don't know where else to go.

774
01:02:15,387 --> 01:02:18,802
Of course I'll help.
But you have to tell me what's wrong.

775
01:02:19,770 --> 01:02:21,722
Is it too late for me?

776
01:02:21,723 --> 01:02:24,602
Is it too late for me to be saved?

777
01:02:24,603 --> 01:02:26,779
It's never too late.

778
01:02:26,780 --> 01:02:29,946
Even if someone chose
a terrible path for me?

779
01:02:29,947 --> 01:02:31,866
You're responsible
for your own salvation.

780
01:02:31,867 --> 01:02:34,233
- God lets you make that choice for yourself.
- You're sure?

781
01:02:34,234 --> 01:02:36,599
Of course.

782
01:02:36,634 --> 01:02:38,554
I choose it then.

783
01:02:38,555 --> 01:02:41,008
I choose salvation.

784
01:02:41,819 --> 01:02:44,313
I'm really glad you came to me, Molly.

785
01:02:44,314 --> 01:02:46,234
You won't regret this journey.
I promise.

786
01:02:46,235 --> 01:02:48,282
No!
I can't take a journey!

787
01:02:48,283 --> 01:02:51,034
I need you to help me now.
I'm running out of time.

788
01:02:51,035 --> 01:02:53,275
Time for what?

789
01:02:53,276 --> 01:02:55,003
I need protection...

790
01:02:55,004 --> 01:02:57,338
before it's too late.

791
01:02:57,915 --> 01:03:00,882
Please help me.

792
01:03:03,004 --> 01:03:05,392
Come with me.

793
01:03:13,051 --> 01:03:15,418
This way.

794
01:03:43,642 --> 01:03:46,032
Put this on.

795
01:03:48,955 --> 01:03:51,035
This will work, right?

796
01:03:51,036 --> 01:03:53,882
If you accept Jesus Christ into your heart,
you will be purified.

797
01:03:53,883 --> 01:03:57,232
You'll be born of water and the Spirit,
and you will be saved.

798
01:04:00,700 --> 01:04:02,746
That's what you want, isn't it?

799
01:04:02,747 --> 01:04:05,136
Yes.

800
01:04:05,913 --> 01:04:08,248
Come with me.

801
01:04:24,219 --> 01:04:27,545
Do you believe and trust in God, the
Father Almighty, maker of heaven and earth...

802
01:04:27,546 --> 01:04:30,425
who gave us his only son
to die for us?

803
01:04:30,426 --> 01:04:33,626
Do you believe in his son, Jesus Christ,
who was crucified for our sins...

804
01:04:33,627 --> 01:04:36,506
rose from the dead,
and is the only way to salvation?

805
01:04:36,507 --> 01:04:38,006
Do you believe and trust
in the Holy Spirit...

806
01:04:38,007 --> 01:04:43,281
who enables us to receive God's word,
repent, and believe the Gospels?

807
01:04:44,156 --> 01:04:46,074
Say if you believe.

808
01:04:46,075 --> 01:04:48,465
I-

809
01:04:52,058 --> 01:04:53,977
Yes.

810
01:04:53,978 --> 01:04:58,074
Do you wish to be baptized
to seal this faith?

811
01:04:58,075 --> 01:05:00,058
Yes.

812
01:05:00,059 --> 01:05:02,229
Close your eyes.

813
01:05:18,841 --> 01:05:21,231
Is it done?

814
01:05:22,842 --> 01:05:24,727
<i>What's wrong?</i>

815
01:05:24,762 --> 01:05:28,209
Do you know
where my grandmother's a nurse?

816
01:05:29,594 --> 01:05:31,674
Clayton.

817
01:05:31,675 --> 01:05:35,188
I know about your mother, Molly,
and what she believes.

818
01:05:36,219 --> 01:05:39,665
Jesus, forgive me for my sins.

819
01:05:40,474 --> 01:05:42,392
This will save your soul!

820
01:05:42,393 --> 01:05:44,310
You promised to help me!

821
01:05:44,345 --> 01:05:47,509
I am! I'm saving you!
Now you'll be with God!

822
01:05:47,994 --> 01:05:50,776
Stay down!
I'm sending you to heaven!

823
01:05:50,907 --> 01:05:52,761
I know what you are!

824
01:05:52,762 --> 01:05:56,664
I can't let you live!
Don't you see? This is the only way!

825
01:06:11,098 --> 01:06:13,716
<i>Oh.</i>

826
01:06:16,058 --> 01:06:18,074
I'm sorry.

827
01:06:38,361 --> 01:06:41,466
Molly? My God!
Are you okay?

828
01:06:41,467 --> 01:06:44,026
What happened?
Come here.

829
01:06:44,027 --> 01:06:47,920
Get in the car. It's gonna be okay.

830
01:06:52,506 --> 01:06:55,123
Are you gonna
tell me what happened?

831
01:06:55,963 --> 01:06:59,737
There are a lot of things
that you don't know about me.

832
01:06:59,738 --> 01:07:02,521
Terrible things.

833
01:07:02,522 --> 01:07:05,337
Well, I could probably say
the exact same thing, Molly.

834
01:07:05,338 --> 01:07:07,256
No!

835
01:07:07,257 --> 01:07:09,113
You don't understand!

836
01:07:09,114 --> 01:07:13,271
Okay, so explain it to me.
Please, Molly. Just tell me what happened.

837
01:07:31,514 --> 01:07:35,833
Hey, Mr. Hartley.
Is, um- Is Molly here?

838
01:07:35,834 --> 01:07:37,498
No. No.

839
01:07:37,499 --> 01:07:39,418
I just-

840
01:07:39,419 --> 01:07:42,617
- I got her a birthday present, so-
- Yeah, I'll take it.

841
01:07:42,618 --> 01:07:45,007
Okay.

842
01:07:46,235 --> 01:07:48,152
Is Molly okay?

843
01:07:48,153 --> 01:07:50,552
Yeah.
I'm sure she's fine.

844
01:07:50,553 --> 01:07:56,304
Um... do you have any idea
where she might be?

845
01:08:05,787 --> 01:08:08,505
Say something.

846
01:08:08,506 --> 01:08:12,152
I just think you're tired.
Just go inside and get some sleep.

847
01:08:12,153 --> 01:08:14,073
I knew you wouldn't believe me.

848
01:08:14,074 --> 01:08:16,313
Well, what am I supposed to say, Molly?

849
01:08:16,314 --> 01:08:19,576
Do you really expect me to believe
that your soul belongs to the devil?

850
01:08:19,577 --> 01:08:23,952
I mean, don't you realize
how insane that sounds?

851
01:08:26,970 --> 01:08:29,849
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to say it like that.

852
01:08:29,850 --> 01:08:32,345
No. You're right.

853
01:08:32,346 --> 01:08:34,265
Maybe I am just like my mother.

854
01:08:34,266 --> 01:08:37,881
Maybe- Maybe I am just I-
losing my mind.

855
01:08:37,882 --> 01:08:40,921
No!
There's nothing wrong with you.

856
01:08:40,922 --> 01:08:43,801
I don't know what to do.

857
01:08:43,802 --> 01:08:47,994
We just need to get the hell outta here, away
from your dad, away from this whole damn town.

858
01:08:47,995 --> 01:08:49,914
And go where?

859
01:08:49,915 --> 01:08:54,457
My dad keeps a lot of money in the safe,
enough to go practically anywhere.

860
01:08:54,458 --> 01:08:56,792
Just you and me.

861
01:08:59,547 --> 01:09:01,935
You don't have to do this.

862
01:09:08,634 --> 01:09:11,317
I'll be right back.
Okay?

863
01:09:47,546 --> 01:09:49,225
This is Amelia Emerson.

864
01:09:49,226 --> 01:09:50,704
Please leave me
a detailed message...

865
01:09:50,705 --> 01:09:54,035
and I'll return the call as soon
as possible. Thank you.

866
01:09:54,070 --> 01:09:58,070
Dr. Emerson, it's Molly.

867
01:09:59,674 --> 01:10:04,084
Something's happened and I'm in trouble,
and I don't know what to do.

868
01:10:05,465 --> 01:10:07,896
I'm at Joseph Young's...

869
01:10:07,897 --> 01:10:10,351
and I'm really scared.

870
01:10:12,792 --> 01:10:14,713
If you could call me back-

871
01:10:14,714 --> 01:10:16,633
<i>Molly!</i>

872
01:10:41,465 --> 01:10:43,555
Joseph?

873
01:10:54,202 --> 01:10:56,291
Joseph?

874
01:11:04,442 --> 01:11:06,530
Joseph?

875
01:11:16,633 --> 01:11:18,723
Joseph?

876
01:11:26,138 --> 01:11:28,227
Joseph?

877
01:12:15,417 --> 01:12:17,805
What're you doing?

878
01:12:18,457 --> 01:12:20,440
Are you surprised?

879
01:12:20,441 --> 01:12:22,359
<i>It's your birthday, right?</i>

880
01:12:22,360 --> 01:12:24,185
Tomorrow.

881
01:12:24,186 --> 01:12:26,105
Well, it's almost tomorrow.

882
01:12:26,106 --> 01:12:29,334
So, happy birthday a few minutes early.

883
01:12:30,874 --> 01:12:33,464
Come on.
Don't you wanna blow out the candle?

884
01:12:35,418 --> 01:12:37,432
I wanna get outta here.

885
01:12:37,433 --> 01:12:39,416
But what about our party?

886
01:12:39,417 --> 01:12:43,606
Okay, you're scaring me.
What the hell is wrong with you?

887
01:12:45,274 --> 01:12:47,224
<i>Joseph, let's go.</i>

888
01:12:47,225 --> 01:12:49,560
Let's go!

889
01:12:51,192 --> 01:12:52,883
Fine.

890
01:12:54,553 --> 01:12:57,270
<i>Dr. Emerson,
you got my message.</i>

891
01:12:57,305 --> 01:13:00,824
- Message?
- I called you. I... I left you a message.

892
01:13:00,825 --> 01:13:03,444
No. No message.

893
01:13:06,296 --> 01:13:10,105
Then... what're you doing here?

894
01:13:10,106 --> 01:13:12,441
Well, it's your birthday, Molly.
Of course I'm here.

895
01:13:12,442 --> 01:13:14,584
<i>Just a few more minutes now.
How does it feel?</i>

896
01:13:16,185 --> 01:13:18,136
How does what feel?

897
01:13:18,137 --> 01:13:20,471
Your new life.

898
01:13:21,209 --> 01:13:24,919
<i>We're all here for you, Molly.
We've watched you grow.</i>

899
01:13:24,920 --> 01:13:28,761
<i>- We've chosen you.
- No.</i>

900
01:13:28,762 --> 01:13:31,151
No?

901
01:13:32,601 --> 01:13:34,989
You knew all along?

902
01:13:36,793 --> 01:13:38,361
You lied to me?

903
01:13:38,362 --> 01:13:40,406
You promised to help me!

904
01:13:40,441 --> 01:13:43,193
<i>He is helping you.
We're all helping you.</i>

905
01:13:43,194 --> 01:13:45,233
You're the one, Molly.

906
01:13:45,977 --> 01:13:48,792
Don't you know how lucky you are?

907
01:13:48,793 --> 01:13:51,863
<i>- Lucky?
- You'll have power like no one before you.</i>

908
01:13:51,864 --> 01:13:54,263
I didn't choose this!

909
01:13:54,264 --> 01:13:56,560
Your mother and father
made that choice for you.

910
01:13:56,561 --> 01:13:59,984
They did it to save my life.
That is not a choice.

911
01:13:59,985 --> 01:14:01,305
Of course it is.

912
01:14:01,306 --> 01:14:05,144
But human weakness
has its consequences. It always has.

913
01:14:05,145 --> 01:14:08,215
<i>D... D... Daddy!</i>

914
01:14:08,216 --> 01:14:10,297
I'm so sorry, Molly!

915
01:14:10,298 --> 01:14:12,888
<i>I didn't... I didn't...</i>

916
01:14:12,889 --> 01:14:16,217
I didn't mean
for any of this to happen.

917
01:14:16,218 --> 01:14:18,871
I'm here to make you an offer.

918
01:14:21,113 --> 01:14:23,351
I didn't believe.

919
01:14:23,352 --> 01:14:25,463
We gave you exactly what you wanted.

920
01:14:25,464 --> 01:14:28,600
Then take me!
It was my mistake! Take me!

921
01:14:28,601 --> 01:14:32,057
God, forgive me.
I- I have sinned.

922
01:14:32,058 --> 01:14:35,256
<i>- I renounce Satan and all-
- What can God offer you?</i>

923
01:14:35,257 --> 01:14:38,776
We've given you everything-
your very life.

924
01:14:38,777 --> 01:14:41,113
And now you have great power
ahead of you.

925
01:14:41,114 --> 01:14:44,344
- I don't want it!
- You will.

926
01:14:44,345 --> 01:14:47,351
God always gives us a choice.

927
01:14:47,352 --> 01:14:51,726
Is that what you think?
God gives you a choice?

928
01:14:55,320 --> 01:14:58,903
Your parents determined your fate.
They turned their back on God.

929
01:14:58,904 --> 01:15:00,696
They made a pact.

930
01:15:00,697 --> 01:15:02,616
Maybe if you kill your father...

931
01:15:02,617 --> 01:15:05,145
the pact will be dissolved.

932
01:15:05,180 --> 01:15:06,579
What?

933
01:15:06,580 --> 01:15:11,471
<i>Of course I can't offer you that choice,
but... maybe God can.</i>

934
01:15:11,640 --> 01:15:13,239
No. No!

935
01:15:13,240 --> 01:15:16,760
Go ahead. Do it.
Just do it.

936
01:15:16,761 --> 01:15:19,149
Go on.

937
01:15:24,377 --> 01:15:26,798
Sweetie, I love you.

938
01:15:28,280 --> 01:15:31,159
- It's... It's the only way.
- Just do it.

939
01:15:31,160 --> 01:15:33,429
<i>Please do it.</i>

940
01:15:34,424 --> 01:15:36,845
I'm sorry.

941
01:15:40,279 --> 01:15:43,415
<i>I love you.</i>

942
01:15:43,416 --> 01:15:45,553
I've always loved you.

943
01:15:46,520 --> 01:15:48,462
No! No!

944
01:15:49,112 --> 01:15:51,314
No, no, no, no!

945
01:16:01,656 --> 01:16:04,371
You've always belonged to us.

946
01:16:08,441 --> 01:16:10,709
Welcome.

947
01:16:11,416 --> 01:16:13,805
<i>We've been waiting.</i>

948
01:16:19,127 --> 01:16:22,264
<i>The patient confessed to the murder
and was brought in about a week ago.</i>

949
01:16:22,265 --> 01:16:24,664
<i>There were several
attempted suicides...</i>

950
01:16:24,665 --> 01:16:28,886
<i>as well as paranoid
and religious delusions.</i>

951
01:16:28,887 --> 01:16:32,215
I know this is a lot to take in.

952
01:16:32,216 --> 01:16:35,095
We've had him
under observation for a week.

953
01:16:35,096 --> 01:16:38,134
<i>So far there's been no change.</i>

954
01:16:38,135 --> 01:16:40,818
I think some interaction with you
might draw him out of his shell.

955
01:16:43,076 --> 01:16:45,719
I can't.
I need to move on.

956
01:16:45,720 --> 01:16:48,182
Don't give up on him.
He's your father.

957
01:16:48,183 --> 01:16:49,879
Not anymore.

958
01:16:49,880 --> 01:16:53,559
Miss Hartley, is there
something you wanna tell me?

959
01:16:53,560 --> 01:16:55,959
It's just the way
things were meant to be.

960
01:16:55,960 --> 01:16:59,668
I know you'll take
really good care of him.

961
01:17:01,016 --> 01:17:02,534
<i>On a personal note...</i>

962
01:17:02,535 --> 01:17:06,296
<i>I would like to thank Huntington Prep
for not only welcoming me into their school...</i>

963
01:17:06,297 --> 01:17:08,950
but for endowing me with
the honor of valedictorian.

964
01:17:08,951 --> 01:17:13,590
<i>In closing, I truly believe that
each one of us has a special destiny...</i>

965
01:17:13,591 --> 01:17:16,567
<i>and we owe it to the world
to fulfill that destiny.</i>

966
01:17:16,568 --> 01:17:19,032
We are the generation
who will change the world...

967
01:17:19,033 --> 01:17:21,303
like no one has
changed it before us.

968
01:17:21,304 --> 01:17:23,223
You can count on it.

969
01:17:23,224 --> 01:17:25,143
Good luck, everyone!

970
01:17:27,576 --> 01:17:30,925
<i>¶¶</i>

971
01:17:39,225 --> 01:17:41,911
Shall we?

972
01:17:41,912 --> 01:17:44,215
<i>- Congratulations, Molly.
- Thank you.</i>

973
01:17:44,216 --> 01:17:46,260
See you soon.

